# Technology Stack Recommendations

This document provides technology recommendations for building a fleet maintenance scheduling system, with rationale for each choice.

## Stack Overview

```typescript
interface RecommendedStack {
  backend: {
    primary: 'TypeScript + Node.js (Bun runtime)';
    solver: 'Python (HiGHS + OR-Tools)';
    api: 'Hono framework';
  };

  database: {
    primary: 'PostgreSQL 16+';
    timeSeries: 'TimescaleDB extension';
    cache: 'Redis';
  };

  frontend: {
    framework: 'React 18+ with TypeScript';
    meta: 'Next.js or Astro';
    visualization: 'ECharts';
  };

  infrastructure: {
    containers: 'Docker';
    orchestration: 'Docker Compose or Kubernetes';
    cloud: 'AWS/GCP/Azure agnostic';
  };
}
```

## Backend: TypeScript + Bun

### Why TypeScript

```typescript
interface TypeScriptBenefits {
  typeSafety: 'Catch errors at compile time';
  developer: 'Excellent IDE support, refactoring';
  ecosystem: 'Largest package ecosystem (npm)';
  hiring: 'Large developer pool';
  fullStack: 'Same language frontend and backend';
}
```

### Why Bun Runtime

```typescript
interface BunBenefits {
  performance: '3-4x faster than Node.js';
  native: 'TypeScript without transpilation';
  bundler: 'Built-in bundler and test runner';
  compatibility: 'Node.js API compatible';
  modern: 'ESM-first, Web APIs built-in';
}
```

### Setup Example

```bash
# Initialize Bun project
bun init

# Install dependencies
bun add hono drizzle-orm postgres zod
bun add -d typescript @types/node
